OL,3,CNHS and health department officials
OL,4,C'out of ideas' for transforming care `
OL,5,CMPs
OL,7,F"The evidence given to our inquiry
OL,8,Fexposes the perennial weaknesses with
OL,9,Fwhich those scrutinising this
OL,10,Fcountry's health systems are now very
OL,11,Ffamiliar.
OL,13,F"We therefore have a simple message
OL,14,Ffor those senior officials responsible
OL,15,Ffor delivery.
OL,17,F"Truly fresh ideas and radical energy
OL,18,Fmust be generated to meet the scale of
OL,19,Fwhat is required ` on community
OL,20,Fhealthcare, on prevention, on digital
OL,21,Ftransformation.
