OL,5,CMPs
OL,7,F"According to official ONS (Office for
OL,8,FNational Statistics) measures, long-
OL,9,Fterm productivity gains in the NHS
OL,10,Faveraged 0.6% a year over the period
OL,11,F1996`97 to 2018`19. But productivity
OL,12,Fsubsequently fell and has yet to
OL,13,Frecover fully.
OL,15,F"The NHS has 19% more staff compared
OL,16,Fto before the pandemic but is only
OL,17,Fseeing 14% more patients. Workforce
OL,18,Fissues such as sickness and absence
OL,19,Fcontinue to impact productivity.
OL,26,@oD@AOUwD@AOU
